sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Clin as ED clinician
    participant ED as ED node
    participant Peer as Sibling / parent (swarm)
    participant ICU as Receiving node

    Note over ED,ICU: WAN is DOWN — both nodes operate locally<br/>(AP: availability over consistency)

    Clin->>ED: Write note + order CT
    activate ED
    ED->>ED: Sign Ed25519/COSE, HLC.tick, commit locally
    ED->>ED: Fold CT into a signed event reference,<br/>stage blob chunks locally
    deactivate ED

    Note over ED,ICU: Patient transferred mid-partition — no scope is "reassigned"<br/>(§6.4: a transfer gives a node reason to ASSEMBLE the patient)

    Note over ED,ICU: ── Link returns ──

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
    Note over ED,ICU: FAST LANE — eager event plane (small, latency-bound, JSON)
    ICU->>ED: request EventsAfter wall/counter watermark
    ED-->>ICU: verbatim signed event bytes, refs included
    ICU->>ICU: verify_self_described — refuse if it does not verify
    ICU->>ICU: INSERT ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING — set-union
    ICU->>ICU: HLC.merge — local clock never falls behind
    Note right of ICU: Chart now shows the note +<br/>"CT exists" — before any pixel arrives
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 225)
    Note over ED,ICU: SLOW LANE — lazy byte tier (chunked, budgeted, swarm, zero-trust)
    loop each missing 256 KiB chunk — resumable, skip indices already stored
        ICU->>Peer: request BlobSlice addr/offset/len
        Peer-->>ICU: binary frame found/total_len/slice
        ICU->>ICU: verify_slice vs BLAKE3 root — reject and try next peer if it lies
        ICU->>ICU: sleep budget_ms — preemptible, events interleave between chunks
    end
    ICU->>ICU: assemble, re-verify whole blob, flip to present
    end

    Note over ED,ICU: Convergence — byte-identical content addresses on both sides.<br/>Every projection shows freshness + known-missing parts (honest assembly).
